# Plan: Auto-Route Questions to Avi & Generic Processing Pills

## Problem Summary
When user posts "What is the weather like in los gatos?":
1. The post is created successfully
2. "Waiting for Avi" pill appears
3. But Avi never responds because `isAviQuestion()` requires explicit "avi" mention

## User Requirements
1. **Avi should auto-respond to ALL questions** that don't explicitly @mention another agent
2. **Change pills to generic "Waiting for agents"** instead of Avi-specific text

---

## Implementation Plan

### Part 1: Backend - Auto-Route Questions to Avi

**File: `/workspaces/agent-feed/api-server/server.js`**

#### 1.1 Modify `isAviQuestion()` function (lines 263-278)

Replace the current logic with question detection:

```javascript
function isAviQuestion(content) {
  const lowerContent = content.toLowerCase();

  // Priority 1: Skip if contains URL (goes to link-logger)
  if (containsURL(content)) {
    return false;
  }

  // Priority 2: Check for explicit @mention of another agent
  // Pattern: @agent-name or @agent (not @avi)
  const agentMentionPattern = /@(link-logger|personal-todos|follow-ups|meeting-prep|page-builder|skills|get-to-know-you|feedback|ideas)(-agent)?\b/i;
  if (agentMentionPattern.test(content)) {
    return false; // Route to mentioned agent, not Avi
  }

  // Priority 3: Explicit Avi mention - always route to Avi
  if (lowerContent.includes('avi') || lowerContent.includes('λvi')) {
    return true;
  }

  // Priority 4: Question detection - route to Avi as default responder
  // Check for question mark
  if (content.includes('?')) {
    return true;
  }

  // Check for question words at start
  const questionPattern = /^(what|how|why|when|where|who|which|can|could|would|should|is|are|do|does|will)\b/i;
  if (questionPattern.test(content.trim())) {
    return true;
  }

  return false;
}
```

#### 1.2 Add word boundary fix for "avi" detection

To prevent false positives like "aviation" or "navigate":

```javascript
// More precise avi detection (add before the includes check)
const aviPattern = /\bavi\b|\bλvi\b|@avi\b/i;
if (aviPattern.test(content)) {
  return true;
}
```

